<dl id="n35208g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35208g">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35208g"> 208(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Collect Pond</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><i>Water Supply</i>. &mdash;The water supply of the colonial city was derived from wells and from the many fresh-water streams and ponds which have now almost without exception been filled in. A system, drawing water from Collect Pond, was installed in 1774-1776 by Christopher Coles (1738-1821), but this was never in actual operation. <small> &ldquo;NEW YORK&rdquo; <a name="EBNY" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBNY"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 619</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
